Dry, warm weather overWestern Europe sugar beet areas this week will allow plantingto progress rapidly, private forecaster Accu-Weather Inc said.    Sugar beet areas in Britain will be dry and warm Thursdayand Friday while beet areas from France to West Germany willhave dry, seasonable weather, becoming warmer.    But damp, chilly weather will delay planting in all Sovietbeet areas, it said. Eastern Soviet sugar beet areas were windyyesterday with rain and snow showers. Water equivalent amountswere 0.10 of an inch.    Showers or snow flurries will linger today and up to 0.30of an inch of rain is likely tomorrow. Reuter&#3;